Answer Question 3:

Event Bubbling is when an event starts on a target element and then moves upward to its 
parent elements in the DOM.
When a child element is clicked:
The event runs on the child first.
Then it goes to the parent.
Then to the grandparent
and continues upward to the document.
This upward movement of an event is called Event Bubbling.


